<enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132114729,imgsize-180108.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Neither side thinks they've lost': Iran determined to keep Hormuz control, even by force]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132111712.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/neither-side-thinks-theyve-lost-iran-determined-to-keep-hormuz-control-even-by-force/articleshow/132111712.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/neither-side-thinks-theyve-lost-iran-determined-to-keep-hormuz-control-even-by-force/articleshow/132111712.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T17:14:57+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132114427,imgsize-72733.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This Arab proverb explains why faith alone isn't enough: ‘Trust in God, but tie your camel’]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132113759.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The profound proverb, 'Tie your camel and trust in God,' expresses the crucial balance between faith and practical efforts. Originating from Islamic teachings, it conveys that we should rely on divine support for uncontrollable aspects but also take charge of our duties. This timeless advice continues to be significant, serving as a reminder for individuals to proactively tackle life's uncertainties while maintaining their spiritual convictions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/this-arab-proverb-explains-why-faith-alone-isnt-enough-trust-in-god-but-tie-your-camel/articleshow/132113759.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/this-arab-proverb-explains-why-faith-alone-isnt-enough-trust-in-god-but-tie-your-camel/articleshow/132113759.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T17:15:00+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132113820,imgsize-185914.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[English proverb of the day: ‘The pot calling the kettle black’ — how an old kitchen saying became a lesson in recognising our own flaws]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132112733.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The saying, "the pot calling the kettle black," perfectly illustrates the irony of hypocrisy, where people spotlight the flaws of others while harboring similar shortcomings. This proverb, which dates back to 17th-century England, is still pertinent in modern conversations, serving as a powerful reminder to embrace self-reflection before casting judgment, as the accusations often reveal more about the accuser than the accused.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/english-proverb-of-the-day-the-pot-calling-the-kettle-black-how-an-old-kitchen-saying-became-a-lesson-in-recognising-our-own-flaws/articleshow/132112733.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/english-proverb-of-the-day-the-pot-calling-the-kettle-black-how-an-old-kitchen-saying-became-a-lesson-in-recognising-our-own-flaws/articleshow/132112733.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T16:41:39+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132113719,imgsize-203081.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[ExtraEmily banned on Twitch after a near crash changes her latest livestream]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132098973.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[ExtraEmily has been banned from Twitch after a June 28 IRL stream showed her nearly crashing while reading chat during a drive. The incident revived concerns about distracted driving and followed previous controversies, including a viewbotting dispute and an earlier driving-related suspension. The latest ban has again sparked debate over safety rules for livestreamers and the responsibility creators have while broadcasting in public.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/extraemily-banned-on-twitch-after-a-near-crash-changes-her-latest-livestream/articleshow/132098973.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/extraemily-banned-on-twitch-after-a-near-crash-changes-her-latest-livestream/articleshow/132098973.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-30T23:17:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132098939,imgsize-90671.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[She died before they were born. So why is Gen Z obsessed with Princess Diana's every clip?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132111629.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/she-died-before-they-were-born-so-why-is-gen-z-obsessed-with-princess-dianas-every-clip/articleshow/132111629.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/she-died-before-they-were-born-so-why-is-gen-z-obsessed-with-princess-dianas-every-clip/articleshow/132111629.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-01T16:14:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Prisha Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132112874,imgsize-40816.cms"/></item><ite